    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.8.0-dev+458-gf479dd0bbe\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nidk\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n5.17.15-1-MANJARO\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.25.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nCreate infinite hi groups\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDon't core dump\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nI had an unrelated bug that caused the creation of infinite highlight groups, eventually hitting the 20k limit. However, upon hitting the limit, Neovim usually coredumps. It would be nice if it wouldn't core dump so i'd be easier to debug.\r\n\r\nManaged to get this one small line out of it:\r\n```\r\nnvim: /var/tmp/pamac-build-tyler/neovim-git/src/neovim-git/src/nvim/message.c:2400: msg_scroll_flush: Assertion `pos_delta >= 0' failed. \r\n[1]    3494094 IOT instruction (core dumped)  nvim .\r\n```",
